# Env files — .env holds real per-developer secrets, never commit it.
# .env.docker ships tracked: docker-compose depends on it and it currently
# holds only fixed dev-container values (db/redis creds, Stripe test placeholders,
# no real secret). If it ever gains a real value, split it and ignore that file instead.
.env
!.env.example

